<|r1|><**EU actions to combat climate change**
 
| EU Action area | Key measures / initiatives | Reference |
><|subclaims|><The EU has actions to combat climate change.><The actions are listed in the table.><end||subclaims><|cite|><|None|><end||cite><|unsupported|><|explain|><The claim is too vague and does not provide any specific information that can be verified. The table appears to be a summary of EU actions to combat climate change, but it is not a claim that can be supported or refuted.><end||explain><end||r><|r2|><|----------------|---------------------------|-----------|
 | Governance & reporting | Governance Regulation (Articles 17 & 19) requires Member States to report on climate mitigation, adaptation and justice (direct/indirect mentions). | [[2]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/thematic-briefings/climate-change/climate-risks-to-society/european-countries-eu-27-iceland-and-switzerland) |
><|subclaims|><The EU has a Governance Regulation.><The regulation requires Member States to report on climate mitigation, adaptation, and justice.><end||subclaims><|cite|><|s1|><end||cite><|supported|><|explain|><The first sentence of the context mentions the Governance Regulation of the Energy Union and Climate Action, which requires Member States to report on climate mitigation, adaptation, and justice.><end||explain><end||r><|r3|><| Emissions‑reduction targets | 70 % cut in total GHG emissions by 2030 (vs 1990) under the “Fit for 55” package; sector‑specific pathways modelled in the MIX‑55 scenario. | [[29]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/main-report/eu-greenhouse-gas-emissions), [[31]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/thematic-briefings/climate-change/greenhouse-gas-emissions/eu-greenhouse-gas-emissions-sectorial-progress-towards-2030) |
 | HFC phase‑down | EU F‑gas Regulation imposes a step‑wise reduction of hydrofluorocarbons; progress shown for 2015‑2023. | [[22]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/thematic-briefings/climate-change/ozone-depleting-substances-and-fluorinated-greenhouse-gases/eu-progress-under-the-hydrofluorocarbon-1) |
><|subclaims|><The EU has emissions-reduction targets.><The targets include a 70% cut in total GHG emissions by 2030.><end||subclaims><|cite|><|s29|,|s31|><end||cite><|supported|><|explain|><The context mentions the EU's emissions-reduction targets, including a 70% cut in total GHG emissions by 2030, and provides references to specific documents that support this claim.><end||explain><end||r><|r4|><| Public funding for climate‑related technologies | € billions of public funding allocated across innovation phases (research, demonstration, market uptake) for 2021‑2027. | [[16]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/main-report/available-public-funding-for-climate) |
 | Adaptation policies | EU monitors and supports national climate‑adaptation policies (2015‑2025) and maps national climate laws. | [[6]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/thematic-briefings/climate-change/governance-of-climate-change-mitigation-and-adaptation/overview-of-climate-governance-in-the-eu) |
><|subclaims|><The EU has public funding for climate-related technologies.><The funding is allocated across innovation phases.><end||subclaims><|cite|><|s16|><end||cite><|supported|><|explain|><The context mentions the EU's public funding for climate-related technologies, including the allocation of funding across innovation phases, and provides a reference to a specific document that supports this claim.><end||explain><end||r><|r5|><| LULUCF obligations | Member States must comply with the EU LULUCF Regulation to ensure forest and land‑use sinks contribute to climate targets. | [[19]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/countries/denmark/total-greenhouse-gas-emissions) |
 | Sector‑specific progress | Emissions from energy, transport, agriculture and other sectors are tracked; modelled 2030 pathways guide required ambition. | [[29]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/main-report/eu-greenhouse-gas-emissions), [[31]](https://www.eea.europa.eu/en/europe-environment-2025/thematic-briefings/climate-change/greenhouse-gas-emissions/eu-greenhouse-gas-emissions-sectorial-progress-towards-2030) |
><|subclaims|><The EU has LULUCF obligations.><The obligations require Member States to comply with the EU LULUCF Regulation.><end||subclaims><|cite|><|s19|><end||cite><|supported|><|explain|><The context mentions the EU's LULUCF obligations, including the requirement for Member States to comply with the EU LULUCF Regulation, and provides a reference to a specific document that supports this claim.><end||explain><end||r><|r6|><
*All information is drawn from the Europe’s environment 2025 data set.><|subclaims|><The information is drawn from the Europe’s environment 2025 data set.><The data set is the sole source of the information.><end||subclaims><|cite|><|None|><end||cite><|unsupported|><|explain|><The claim is too vague and does not provide any specific information that can be verified. The context does mention the Europe’s environment 2025 data set, but it does not explicitly state that all information is drawn from this data set.><end||explain><end||r>
